                    </div>
                    <span>If you learn best by repetitive exposure (i.e., flashcards), this book is for you.  Rita's Hot Topics allows you to "quiz" yourself or work with a partner or group to study for the PMP exam.  I recently passed the PMP and was helped by using this book (although it wasn't my only resource).  The CD version of this book is also helpful, as it can be used in the car or at home, and the built-in timing forces you to work on answering questions quickly and correctly.  On the negative side, I found it easy to get bored with this format, and ended up relying upon the book more heavily.  Overall, however, it was worth the money I spent on it [($$$)].</span>
                  
              
